tip.text: Superb food and comfortable space. Authentic Sichuan cuisine. Must order: Sichuan Beef (main) and spicy cucumber (appetizer). Another added bonus - free corkage!

venue.name: Sijie Sichuan Private Kitchen (四姐川菜)

tip.text: Inconsistent std of service. One staff who is the most friendly & service oriented, whereas the rest couldn't be more unhappy. Food is pretty ok though I find there are better Italian food around.
Excellent set lunch and fresh charabashi. Unlimited side dishes in Thursdays. Drool worthy and do go early to queue as there are limited space.
It was an incredible molecular gastronomy journey top with EXCELLENT service. Aston reopened for us becos it missed our reservation. Beautiful food and creation. Love its Razor clam, Tom Kha caviar.

tip.text: Feels more like a high-end street food restaurant. Taste was too sweet or too salty. pa-nang Wagyu beef was good but fish was waaay overcooked. Give it a miss and hit the street instead.

tip.text: Excellent food here. Good ambience and attentive services. One of the rare few that allow you to portion food according to party size. Great for celebrations and work dinners and dates.
Coffee is FANTASTIC! They make excellent coffee, though the same does not apply for food. I had a piece of steak that had gone off being served. Food is not recommended. Stick to coffee and drinks.
A novelty in eating seafood. Get all down and dirty to thoroughly immerse in this seafood experience even though it's a rather pricey affair. Costs about $450 for 5 adults.
Overcrowded with tourists and prepare to pay tourist price for street food. However its location is the best for convenience and shopping! Many tax-refund shops around.
It sells a wide array of knives starting from few thousand ¥ to one that's ¥300,000! It's an interesting way to discover the art of knives collection. Also, Japanese are well-known in culinary world.

tip.text: A very pretty cafè with good brunch and coffee. It's a little pricey but you'll enjoy it amongst one of the prettiest garden setting. Staff are fluent in English too!
Excellent location to restaurants and bars. Walking distance to Dotonburi. Fuss-free hotel with exceptional services.

tip.text: I'm unimpressed by the hard-selling services by most of their stylists. However my stylist is more decent & direct. Look for her if you don't want hard-sell service staff. Pricing is on the high side
Swanky bar with cover charge of ¥500. Seeing the bartenders at work is like watching a dance. Elegant and interesting. Good selection of whiskies. Ask the staff for recommendation if overwhelmed!

tip.text: 300¥ drinks all night long. They have excellent roast beef! Casual dining but super friendly staff

Absolutely delicious and well made burgers. Tried the "wimpy" burger which is a single patty of the "Fat Bastard". Fresh sesame topped burger bread, substantial filling and medium cooked meat. Superb!

tip.text: Excellent breakfast. I love the lemon salmon and egg bacon roll. They serve great quality coffee and tea. Attentive and friendly staff in a cosy cafe.
Excellent tenderloin and service. All their staff speak good English. Do book in advance.
